<div id="Idea_2988"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/2988-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_2988">No Tax paid Health Insurance and Benefits for any Public Employees&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/4319-4049">Paul D. Kendall</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">7 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">No public employee should be furnished any kind of Health or Life Insurance benefits from our tax dollars by the city, state, or Federal Govt.<br/>If they want these, they should buy them with their own money we paid to them by giving them a tax paid job. They should take their money and buy these life and health insurace bendfits from a private company.( if this company cheats them the company administrators should go to jail for a long time)<br/>Many of us could compete for tax paid jobs, but we dont for one reason or another, and that is ok! <br/>But to give health insurance to these few people and not the rest of the citizens is truly unfair to the general population!<br/>It is an unfair redistribution of our tax monies to a few.<br/></div>
